    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-07-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-07-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="610"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d610">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Japanese Chargé</gloss> to Acting
                        Secretary of State <persName type="to">Adee</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Japan</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-07-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 29, 1905</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to my note No. 42 of to-day’s date,
                    relative to the case of an infraction of the international conventions’ by the
                    commander of the first brigade of the thirty-first division of the Russian army
                    in Manchuria, I have the honor to inform you that I am instructed by the
                    Imperial Government to bring the case in question to the special notice of the
                    United States Government as one of the signatories of the Geneva and Hague
                    conventions.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Eki Hioki.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
